{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f74cec31-b3ba-4939-bc08-98b54d5534b6","content":"I found the following issues in `.template.config/template.json`:\n\n1. **Missing `identity` field** (required) — Every .NET template must have a unique `identity` string (e.g., `\"identity\": \"Test.Template\"`).\n\n2. **Invalid `datatype` on line 9** — `\"invalid-type\"` is not a valid datatype. Valid values are: `bool`, `choice`, `float`, `int`, `hex`, `text`, and `string`.\n\n3. **Missing `$schema`** (recommended) — Adding a `$schema` reference enables editor validation:\n   ```\n   \"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"\n   ```\n\nThe `identity` and `datatype` issues will cause failures when installing or running this template.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7ff38924-32c0-4b77-a683-dac4c4ec9690","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me analyze the template.json file for issues. This is a .NET template configuration file. Let me check for issues:\n\n1. **Missing required fields**: The `template.json` schema requires:\n   - `$schema` - not strictly required but recommended\n   - `author` ✓\n   - `classifications` ✓\n   - `identity` - **MISSING** - this is required\n   - `name` ✓\n   - `shortName` ✓\n   - `sourceName` - optional\n\n2. **Invalid datatype**: Line 9 has `\"datatype\": \"invalid-type\"`. Valid datatypes for template.json parameters are: `bool`, `choice`, `float`, `int`, `hex`, `text`, `string`. `\"invalid-type\"` is not a valid datatype.\n   \nThe `identity` field is required in the template configuration and needs to be added to fix this validation error.","outputTokens":418,"requestId":"33C9:3FE43:1F577F7:231DFDF:69E81967"},"id":"e9c0a156-9c0f-4bcb-92be-9624025bca64","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:42:25.514Z","parentId":"0b23c94e-df05-49ca-8965-308d3888e3f6"}
